Added Unit, and Integration TestsAdded unit tests for many of the classes in the client.  Added newndependencies for the unit tests to the POM file.  Unit tests can benexecuted the `surefire:test` goal, and are executed during the test phase.nnAdded integration tests for the client.  The tests require access toncredentials that can interact with Kinesis, and DynamoDB.  Thenintegration tests can be run by executing then`failsafe:integration-test` goal, or are run as part of thenintegration-test phasenn**Resources in the integration tests are not currently released onncompletion of the integration tests.**n

Enable Travis CI BuildsAdded the Travis CI configuration to enable continous integrationntesting for common JDK version > 1.7.nnMove gpg signing to its own profile to avoid causing issues with thentest, and integration-test phases.n
Copy sqlite Native Libraries, and Use for TestingCopies all the native library version for sqlite during the test compilenphase.  The sqlite native libraries are only needed to run the unit tests.n

Merge Changes for PR#61Merge, and slight adjustment, ofnhttps://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/61.nnThis allows configuration to explicitly set the name of the leasentable.  The table name defaults to the application name which is thencurrent behavior.n

Fix Race Condition on Worker TestThe test 'testWorkerForcefulShutdown' was using Thread.sleep() to createnthe conditions for an interrupted state.  It was possible for the testnto take enough time for the sleep to actually exit before the interruptnwas sent.  This would cause the test to fail.  Changing to a pair ofnsempahores ensures that the test record processor will remain blockednfor the expected amount of time.n

Allow Prioritization of Parent Shard TasksAdded a new interface that allows the worker to prioritize which leasenassignment it will work on next.  When using thenParentsFirstshardprioritization the worker will select parents fornprocessing before selecting children.  This will prevent ShardConsumersnfrom spending time sleeping in the WAITING_ON_PARENT_SHARDS state.n
Merge pull request #95 from pfifer/shard-prioritizationAllow Prioritization of Parent Shard Tasks

Don't Use Checkpoint for Equality in ShardInfoDon't include checkpoint in hashCode/equality for ShardInfo, since itnchanges. Checkpointing would cause the Worker to recreate thenShardConsumer.  Add unit tests that verify the equality constraints.nnRemove the equality test for checkpoint from ShardInfoTests.  Nothingnappears to rely on the checkpoint being part of ShardInfo.nnFix WorkerTest broken in overzealous simplification.n

Version 1.7.0 of the Amazon Kinesis Client Library* Add support for time based iterators ([See GetShardIterator Documentation](http://docs.aws.amazon.com/kinesis/latest/APIReference/API_GetShardIterator.html))n  * [PR #94](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/94)n  The `KinesisClientLibConfiguration` now supports providing an initial time stamp position.n  * This position is only used if there is no current checkpoint for the shard.n  * This setting cannot be used with DynamoDB Streamsn  Resolves [Issue #88](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/issues/88)n* Allow Prioritization of Parent Shards for Task Assignmentn  * [PR #95](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/95)n  The `KinesisClientLibconfiguration` now supports providing a `ShardPrioritization` strategy.  This strategy controls how the `Worker` determines which `ShardConsumer` to call next.  This can improve processing for streams that split often, such as DynamoDB Streams.n* Remove direct dependency on `aws-java-sdk-core`, to allow independent versioning.n  * [PR #92](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/92)n  **You may need to add a direct dependency on aws-java-sdk-core if other dependencies include an older version.**n
Move Version to Next Development VersionAdjusted the version to 1.7.1-SNAPSHOT for current development.n

Feature/multiple cred providers (#111)* Add ability to specify different credential providers for Kinesis, DynamoDB, and CloudWatch.  This is needed when accessing a cross-account Kineses stream using an assumed role.rnrn* Fix copy/paste mistake.rnrn* Update tests.rnrnThanks to rgfindl@

Allow Disabling Shard Sync at Startup (#102)Allow disabling the shard sync at startup if the lease table alreadyrncontains leases.  This will reduce the startup load for larger streamsrnwhen restarted the Kinesis application.

Allow for credential providers with basic arg types (#99)* Add support for configuring DynamoDB endpointrnrnAdding a new field named `dynamoDBEndpoint` to the .properties filernthat gets passed into the KCL multi-lang daemon. We need this abilityrnto point the KCL worker at a local instance of DynamoDB rather than inrnAWS.rnrn* Added the ability to use AWSCredentialsProvider's that require non-empty contructor args e.g. ProfileCredentialsProvider where you provide the profile name to use from your ~/.aws/credentials filernrn* Created a constructor without the dynamoDBEndpoint argument i.e. same arguments before the dynamo change, for backwards compatibilityrn

Allow for a Graceful Shutdown of the Worker (#109)Add a new method to the worker requestShutdown that allows the worker torngracefully shutdown all record processors.  The graceful shutdown givesrnthe record processors a last chance to checkpoint before they'rernterminated.rnrnTo use these new features the record processor must implementrnIShutdownnotificationaware.rn

Release 1.7.1 of the Amazon Kinesis Client Library (#116)* Generalrn  * Allow disabling shard synchronization at startup.rn* Applications can disable shard synchronization at startup.  Disabling shard synchronization can application startup times for very large streams.rn* [PR #102](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/102)rn  * Applications can now request a graceful shutdown, and record processors that implement the IShutdownNotificationAware will be given a chance to checkpoint before being shutdown.rn* This adds a [new interface](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/blob/master/src/main/java/com/amazonaws/services/kinesis/clientlibrary/interfaces/v2/IShutdownNotificationAware.java), and a [new method on Worker](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/blob/master/src/main/java/com/amazonaws/services/kinesis/clientlibrary/lib/worker/Worker.java#L539).rn* [PR #109](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/109)rn* Solves [Issue #79](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/issues/79)rn* MultiLangDaemonrn  * Applications can now use credential provides that accept string parameters.rn* [PR #99](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/99)rn  * Applications can now use different credentials for each service.rn* [PR #111](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/111)

Use ExecutorService.newFixedThreadPool for LeaseRenewerThe existing ThreadPoolExecutor was misconfigured and causednthe thread pool to recycle idle threads continuously. VisualVMnshowed that a thread got recycled about every 3 seconds, creatingnand destroying several hundred threads in about 15 minutes.nnUse ExecutorService.newFixedThreadPool instead, as recommendednby the javadoc for ExecutorService.n

Release 1.7.4 of the Amazon Kinesis Client* Fixed an issue building JavaDoc for Java 8.n  * [Issue #18](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/issues/18)n  * [PR #141](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/141)n* Reduce Throttling Messages to WARN, unless throttling occurs 6 times consecutively.n  * [Issue #4](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/issues/4)n  * [PR #140](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/140)n* Fixed two bugs occurring in requestShutdown.n  * Fixed a bug that prevented the worker from shutting down, via requestShutdown, when no leases were held.n* [Issue #128](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/issues/128)n  * Fixed a bug that could trigger a NullPointerException if leases changed during requestShutdown.n* [Issue #129](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/issues/129)n  * [PR #139](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/139)n* Upgraded the AWS SDK Version to 1.11.91n  * [PR #138](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/138)n* Use an executor returned from `ExecutorService.newFixedThreadPool` instead of constructing it by hand.n  * [PR #135](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/135)n* Correctly initialize DynamoDB client, when endpoint is explicitly set.n  * [PR #142](https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-client/pull/142)n

Trigger Graceful Shutdown for MultiLang Daemon Clients on SIGTERM (#174)When the parent Java process receives a SIGTERM it will now trigger a graceful shutdown of the worker, which dispatches a ShutdownRequestedMessage to all of the record processors.  This will allow record processors a final chance to checkpoint before the lease is terminated.rnrnThis changes is incompatible with current versions of the MultiLang Clients.  A future change will allow older versions MultiLang clients to use newer versions of the Java KCL.

Release 1.8.1 of the Amazon Kinesis Client (#198)Support timeouts for calls to the MultiLang DaemonrnThis adds support for setting a timeout when dispatching records tornthe client record processor. If the record processor doesn't respondrnwithin the timeout the parent Java process will be terminated. Thisrnis a temporary fix to handle cases where the KCL becomes blockedrnwhile waiting for a client record processor.rnrnThe timeout for the this can be set by addingrn  `timeoutInSeconds = <timeout value>`.rnThe default for this is no timeout.rnrnSetting this can cause the KCL to exit suddenly, before using thisrnensure that you have an automated restart for your applicationrnrnRelated #195rnRelated #185

Add Support for Two Phase Commit (#188)Adds support for making two phase commits.  When a checkpoint is started, but fails to complete the next instance of the record processor will receive the attempted checkpoint position at initialization time.

Adding logging for DynamoDB ProvisionedThroughputExceededExcpetion (#212)* Adding logging to ProvisionedThroughputExceededException.rnrn* Addressing CR comments and changing log level from error to warnrnrn* Updated the comments as per cr comments.rn

Allow Configuring GetRecords Calls to Timeout. (#214)It's now possible to configure GetRecords calls to timeout if theyntake to long.  This can be used to terminate a long running request tonensure that record processors continue to make progressnnThis feature was added with contributions from @pfifer, @sahilpalvia,nand @BtXin.n

Release 1.8.2 of the Amazon Kinesis Client for Java (#218)* Add support for two phase checkpointsrn  Applications can now set a pending checkpoint, before completing the checkpoint operation. Once the application has completed its checkpoint steps, the final checkpoint will clear the pending checkpoint.rn  Should the checkpoint fail the attempted sequence number is provided in the InitializationInput#getPendingCheckpointSequenceNumber otherwise the value will be null.rn  * PR #188rn* Support timeouts, and retry for GetRecords calls.rn  Applications can now set timeouts for GetRecord calls to Kinesis.  As part of setting the timeout, the application must also provide a thread pool size for concurrent requests.rn  * PR #214rn* Notification when the lease table is throttledrn  When writes, or reads, to the lease table are throttled a warning will be emitted.  If you're seeing this warning you should increase the IOPs for your lease table to prevent processing delays.rn  * PR #212rn* Support configuring the graceful shutdown timeout for MultiLang Clientsrn  This adds support for setting the timeout that the Java process will wait for the MutliLang client to complete graceful shutdown.  The timeout can be configured by adding shutdownGraceMillis to the properties file set to the number of milliseconds to wait.rn  * PR #204rn

Only advance the shard iterator when we accept a result to returnThis changes the retriever strategy to only accept the shard iteratornwhen we have accepted a result to return.  This is for thenasynchronous retriever where multiple threads may contend for the sameniterator slot.  This ensures only the one selected for the response willnadvance the shard iterator.n

Release 1.8.5 of the Amazon Kinesis Client for Java (#232)* Release 1.8.5 of the Amazon Kinesis Client for JavarnrnRelease 1.8.5 (September 26, 2017)rn* Only advance the shard iterator for the accepted response.  rn  This fixes a race condition in the `KinesisDataFetcher` when it's being used to make asynchronous requests.  The shard iterator is now only advanced when the retriever calls `DataFetcherResult#accept()`.rn  * PR #230rn  * Issue #231rnrnrn

Support Prefetching of RecordsThis adds that ability for the KCL to fetch records while the record processor is busy.  This can help smooth out delays in record process, or retrieving data from Kinesis.  Enabling this does require extra threads for background retrieval.rnrnSettingsrn* dataFetchingStrategy: Which strategy to use to retrieve records.  This can be either DEFAULT or PREFETCH_CACHEDrn* maxCacheByteSize: Retrieval will be paused when the total number of bytes in the cache exceeds this valuern* maxRecordsCount: Retrieval will be paused when the total number of records in the cache exceeds this valuern* maxPendingProcessRecordsInput: Retrieval will be paused when the total number of fulfilled requests in the cache exceeds this value
Shutdown that throws an exception will be retried. (#238)Without this change a transient error on shutdown with reason terminate preventsrnchild shards from starting.
Revert Shutdown that throws an exception will be retried. (#238) (#251)This reverts commit 44437f13610aeff177650a3d6e15545f56395177.rnrnReverted due to Build Failures

Block Fetch Thread When Retrieval Should be Paused (#252)Block the fetching thread when the queue is considered to be full.rnThis ensures that the thread won't spin the CPU when it can't retrievernmore records or bytes.

Spurious update fix (#247)* Handle spurious lease renewal failures gracefully.rnrnIf the request to conditionally update a lease counter in DynamoDB fails, it'srnconsidered a failure to renew the lease. This is a good thing, except if thernrequest failure was just because of connectivity problems. In this case therncounter *did* update in DynamoDB, but the Dynamo client retries the requestrnwhich then fails the update condition (since the lease counter no longerrnmatches expected value).rnrnTo handle this gracefully we opt to get the lease record from Dynamo andrnexamine the lease owner and counter. If it matches what we were expecting,rnthen we consider renewal a success.
Adding logging for long running tasks. (#259)Allow enabling logging for long running tasks.

Correctly Send MaxRecords to SingleRecordsFetcherFactory Fixed #262Fixes #262 rnrnChanging the signture of SingleRecordsFetcherFactory to no longer take maxRecords as the parameter to the constructor. Changed the createRecordsFetcher signature to take maxRecords as a parameter. (#264)

Unit test fixes for retrying when requesting a shutdown. (#267)* Shutdown that throws an exception will be retried.rnrnWithout this change a transient error on shutdown with reason terminate preventsrnchild shards from starting.rnrn* Fixing the tests for the Shutdown fix.rn

Release 1.8.8 of the Amazon Kinesis Client for JavaRelease 1.8.8n* Fixed issues with leases losses due to `ExpiredIteratorException` in `PrefetchGetRecordsCache` and `AsynchronousFetchingStrategy`.n  PrefetchGetRecordsCache will request for a new iterator and start fetching data again.n  * PR#263n* Added warning message for long running tasks.n  * PR#259n* Handling spurious lease renewal failures gracefully.n  Added better handling of DynamoDB failures when updating leases.  These failures would occur when a request to DynamoDB appeared to fail, but was actually successful.n  * PR#247n* ShutdownTask gets retried if the previous attempt on the ShutdownTask fails.n  * PR#267n* Fix for using maxRecords from `KinesisClientLibConfiguration` in `GetRecordsCache` for fetching records.n  * PR#264n

[Issue 210] - Allow unexpected child shards to be ignored (#240)Allow unexpected child shards to be ignoredrnrnnow instead of always throwing an assertion if a child shard has anrnopen parent, consider worker configuration before doing so.  ifrnconfigured to ignore such shards, do not create leases for them duringrnshard sync.  this is intended to mitigate failing worker init whenrnprocessing dynamodb streams with many thousands of shards (which canrnhappen for tables with thousands of partitions).rnrnthis new behavior can be enabled by adding the following to arnconfiguration/properties file:rnrn```rnignoreUnexpectedChildShards = truern```rn

Added cache updating behavior for GetShard (#344)* Added cache updating behavior for GetShardrnrnCustomer are occasionally seeing messages about being unable tornretrieve shard information, which is logged as a warning.  This changernwill allow the shard map to be updated even when there is no re-shardrnoperation.rnrnThis now triggers a shard list update if there is 1000 cache misses,rnor a cache miss occurs when the cache is more than 30 seconds old.rnFor Kinesis the updates will use ListShards, and for DynamoDB Streamsrnit will continue to use DescribeStream.rnrn* Adjust some logging, and the zeroing of cache misses a bitrnrnOnly log about cache refresh if it's the thread doing the cachernrefresh.  If after synchronizing the shard is present, accept thatrnsomeone else loaded the shard map, and move on.rnrnIf the cache was reloaded, and the shard was found the current threadrnwill reset the cache misses.rnrnThe warnings for the cache miss was using a modulo of 1000 which isrnthe maximum value for cache misses, so wasn't to useful.rn

Release 2.0.0 of the Amazon Kinesis Client for Java* Added support for Enhanced Fan Out.n  Enhanced Fan Out provides for lower end to end latency, and increased number of consumers per stream.n  * Records are now delivered via streaming, reducing end-to-end latency.n  * The Amazon Kinesis Client will automatically register a new consumer if required.nWhen registering a new consumer, the Kinesis Client will default to the application name unless configured otherwise.n  * New configuration options are available to configure Enhanced Fan Out.n  * `SubscribeToShard` maintains long lived connections with Kinesis, which in the AWS Java SDK 2.0 is limited by default.nThe `KinesisClientUtil` has been added to assist configuring the `maxConcurrency` of the `KinesisAsyncClient`.n__WARNING: The Amazon Kinesis Client may see significantly increased latency, unless the `KinesisAsyncClient` is configured to have a `maxConcurrency` high enough to allow all leases plus additional usages of the `KinesisAsyncClient`.__nn  | Name| Default | Description |n  |-----------------|---------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|n  | consumerArn | Unset   | The ARN for an already created consumer.  If this is set, the Kinesis Client will not attempt to create a consumer. |n  | streamName  | Unset   | The name of the stream that a consumer should be create for if necessary|n  | consumerName| Unset   | The name of the consumer to create.  If this is not set the applicationName will be used instead.   |n  | applicationName | Unset   | The name of the application.  This is used as the name of the consumer unless consumerName is set.  |nn* Modular Configuration of the Kinesis Clientn  The Kinesis Client has migrated to a modular configuration system, and the `KinesisClientLibConfiguration` class has been removed.n  Configuration has been split into 7 classes.  Default versions of the configuration can be created from the `ConfigsBuilder`.n  Please see the migration guide for more informationn  * `CheckpointConfig`n  * `CoordinatorConfig`n  * `LeaseManagementConfig`n  * `LifecycleConfig`n  * `MetricsConfig`n  * `ProcessorConfig`n  * `RetrievalConfig`nn* Upgraded to AWS Java SDK 2.0n  The Kinesis Client now uses the AWS Java SDK 2.0.  The dependency on AWS Java SDK 1.11 has been removed.n  All configurations will only accept 2.0 clients.n  * When configuring the `KinesisAsyncClient` the `KinesisClientUtil#createKinesisAsyncClient` can be used to configure the Kinesis Clientn  * __If you need support for AWS Java SDK 1.11 you will need to add a direct dependency.__n__When adding a dependency you must ensure that the 1.11 versions of Jackson dependencies are excluded__nPlease see the migration guide for more informationnn* MultiLangDaemon is now a separate modulen  The MultiLangDaemon has been separated to its own Maven module and is no longer available in `amazon-kinesis-client`.  To include the MultiLangDaemon, add a dependency on `amazon-kinesis-client-multilang`.n

Remove a possible deadlock on polling queue fill (#462)* Remove a possible deadlock on polling queue fillrnrnAdding new items to the receive queue for the PrefetchRecordsPublisherrnwhen at capacity would deadlock retrievals as it was already holdingrna lock on this.rnrnThe method addArrivedRecordsInput did not need to be synchronized onrnthis as it didn't change any of the protectedrnstate (requestedResponses). Thisrntest uses RxJava to consume, and notifies the test thread oncernMAX_ITEMS * 3 have been received. This ensures that we cycle throughrnthe queue at least 3 times.rnrn* Removed the upper limit on the retrievalsrnrnThe way RxJava's request management makes it possible that morernrequests than we might expect can happen.rn

Capability of restarting the subscription from last processed batch (#492)* Started to play around with restarting from last processedrnrnAfter a failure the KCL would instead restart from what thernShardConsumer says it last processed.rnrn* Extracted the InternalSubscriber to its own classrnrnExtracted the InternalSubscriber to ShardConsumerSubscriber to makerntesting easier. Added tests for the ShardConsumerSubscriber thatrnverifies error handling and other components of the class.rnrnAdded tests that verify the restart from behavior.rnrn* Moved the ProcessRecordsInputMatcher to its own classrnrn* Initial changes to for restarting of the PrefetchRecordsPublisherrnrn* Remove code coverage configurationrnrn* Switched to using explicit locks to deal with blocking queuernrnWhen the blocking queue is full it would normally enter into a fullyrnparked state, but would continue to hold the lock.rnrnThis changes the process to only block for a second when attempting tornenqueue a response, and if it doesn't succeed check to see if it'srnbeen reset before attempting again.rnrn* Changed locking around the restart, and how fetcher gets updatedrnrnChanged the locking around the restart to use a reader/writer lockrninstead of single lock with a yield.rnrnChanged how the fetcher is reset to not restart from anrnadvanceIteratorTo which would retrieve a new shard iterator.  Insteadrnthe resetIterator method takes both the iterator to start from, thernlast accepted sequence number, and the initial position.rnrn* Changed test to ensure that PositionResetException is thrownrnrnChanged the test to wait for the queue to reach capacity beforernrestarting the PrefetchRecordsPublisher.  This should mostly ensurernthat calling restartFrom will trigger a throw of arnPositionResetException.rnrnAdded @VisibleFortest on the queue since it was already being used in testing.rnrn* Move to snapshotrnrn* Ensure that only one thread can be sending data at a timernrnIn the test the TestPublisher is accessed from two threads: the testrnthread, and the dispatch thread.  Both have the possibility of callingrnsend() under certain conditions.  This changes it so that only one ofrnthe threads can actively be sending data at a time.rnrnTestPublisher#requested was changed to volatile to ensure that callingrncancel can correctly set it to zero.rnrn* Block the test until the blocking thread is in controlrnrnThis test is somewhat of an odd case as it intends to test whatrnhappens when nothing is dispatched to the ShardConsumerSubcriber forrnsome amount of time, but data is queued for dispatch.  To do this wernblock the single thread of the executor with a lock to ensure thatrnitems pile up in the queue so that should the restart work incorrectlyrnwe will see lost data.rn

Fixing exception log messaging with Prefetching (#497)* Changed Prefetch to catch `SdkException` instead of `SdkClientException`rn  * With SDK 2.x service exceptions are of the type `SdkServiceException`rn* Adding `*.iml` to .gitignore

Use an explicit lock for shutdown instead of the general lock (#501)If the Scheduler loses its lease for a shard it will attempt tornshutdown the ShardConsumer processing that shard.  When shutting downrnthe ShardConsumer acquires a lock on `this` and makes the necessaryrnstate changes.rnrnThis becomes an issue if the ShardConsumer is currently processing arnbatch of records as processing of the records is done under therngeneral `this` lock.rnrnWhen these two things combine the Scheduler can become stuck waitingrnon the record processing to complete.rnrnTo fix this the ShardConsumer will now use a specific lock on shutdownrnstate changes to prevent the Scheduler from becoming blocked.rnrnAllow the shutdown state change future to acquire the lockrnrnWhen the ShardConsumer is being shutdown we create a future for thernstate change originally the future needed to acquire the lock beforernattempting to create the future task.  This changes it to acquire thernlock while running on another thread, and complete the shutdown then.

Add SdkException to exception manager of KinesisDataFetcher (#502)The KinesisDataFetcher uses the AWSExceptionManager to translaternexecution exceptions into the expected exceptions.  Currently if thernexception is unexpected the exception will be wrapped in arnRuntimeException before being returned.  We depend on SdkExceptionsrnbeing the right type where we handle them upstream so we add arnconfiguration for SdkException which should ensure handling works asrnexpected.
